数说疫情0310：武汉战疫验收，意大利病死率5%。
Count 0310: Wuhan acceptance of the epidemic, Italy's fatality rate of 5%.
徐进。
Xu Jin.
财经杂志                      。
Financial magazine.
财经杂志。
Financial magazine.
《财经》杂志官方微信。
An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
中国国家领导人出现在武汉战疫一线，预示武汉歼灭战即将取得彻底胜利；美国政府尚未全力应对；韩国首尔出现大规模集体感染文 |《财经》数据研究员徐进 图 |《财经》视觉中心 编辑 | 郝洲一、武汉战疫进入收官阶段今日国内简述：国内3月9日报告累计确诊病例80754例，新增19例。
The appearance of China's national leaders on the front lines of the Wuhan battle plague heralds a complete victory for Wuhan; the US government has yet to respond fully; Seoul, South Korea, with a massive mass infection; and Caijing Data Center, editor and director of Caijing Vision Center.
国内非湖北地区连续3日实现本地零新增。
China's non-Hubei region 3 consecutive days to achieve zero local growth.
湖北非武汉地区连续5日零新增。
Hubei non-Wuhan area added 5 consecutive days.
武汉连续4日在两位数。
Wuhan is in double digits for 4 consecutive days.
2例输入病例分别来自意大利和西班牙，相关密切接触者已及时集中隔离。
Two of the imported cases came from Italy and Spain, and close contacts have been quarantined in time.
今日上午，中国国家领导人出现在武汉战疫一线，看望慰问医护人员、工作人员、病患和社区居民，安定民心、振奋士气，预示武汉歼灭战即将取得彻底胜利。
This morning, Chinese leaders appeared on the frontline of the Wuhan battle plague to pay tribute to the medical staff, staff, patients and community residents, calm the people and inspire morale, heralding the imminent victory of the Wuhan annihilation war.
A股市场在境外股市崩盘情况下，短暂探低后迅速强劲回升。
A-share market in the face of an offshore stock market crash, a short dip after a rapid and strong rebound.
另有消息表明，武汉机场将可能于3月底逐步复航。
Other reports suggest Wuhan airport could resume flights by the end of March.
二、疫情蔓延已威胁到全球经济图1德国、加拿大首次出现死亡；西班牙跳涨、累计确诊数一夜过千。
The spread of the epidemic has threatened the global economy Figure 1 The first deaths occurred in Germany and Canada, where jumps and cumulative diagnoses topped a thousand a night.
受油价暴跌和全球疫情蔓延所带来的恐慌情绪双重影响，美国三大股指3月9日集体大跌逾7%，道指历史上第二次触发熔断机制，上一次是1997年。
The three main U.S. stock indexes fell more than 7% on March 9, the second time in Dow history that the index triggered a meltdown, the last time in 1997, amid fears of plummeting oil prices and a global epidemic.
世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞表示，由于新冠病毒已在众多国家发酵，“一场全球性流行病的威胁已成为现实”。
"The threat of a global epidemic has become a reality" as the virus has fermented in a number of countries, said World Health Organization Director General Tham Desai.
但谭德塞坚称，“这将是第一次可以控制的大流行”。
But Mr Tanner insists that "this will be the first time that a pandemic can be contained."
图2疫情在欧洲依然犹如脱缰野马一般，一路狂飚，若再不有效阻隔，后果不堪设想。
Fig. 2 The epidemic is still runaway in Europe, with dire consequences if it is not effectively contained.
在世界的另一边，紧随韩国之后，伊朗似乎也逐步稳定住局面，新增确诊连日下降。
On the other side of the world, just after South Korea, Iran seems to be stabilizing, with new diagnoses falling for days.
三、美国10个州宣布紧急状态，白宫承认检测试剂盒不足图3除华盛顿特区外，新冠疫情已扩散至美国36个州。
Ten U.S. states have declared a state of emergency, and the White House admits it has insufficient test kits. Figure 3.
美国确诊感染总数已突破700，目前的情况与10天前的欧洲比较相似。
The total number of confirmed infections in the United States has exceeded 700, and the current situation is similar to that of Europe 10 days ago.
但美国似乎仍未能全力应对。
But the US still seems to be failing to cope.
副总统彭斯3月9日承认，目前没有足够数量的新冠病毒检测工具来应对不断增长的疑似患者检测需求。
Vice President Burns admitted on March 9 that there were not enough tools to detect the new crown virus to meet the growing demand for suspected patients.
高昂的检测费用、医疗物资短缺以及美国民众开始恐慌性抢购，美国政府应对疫情的做法遭到广泛批评。
The government's response has been widely criticized for high testing costs, shortages of medical supplies and panic buying by Americans.
四、欧洲新增势头难以遏制，意大利全国限流，效果仍有待考验图4欧洲不止意大利 ，疫情在德国、法国和西班牙的蔓延势头同样凶猛，累计确诊病例都已过千。
Figure 4 Europe is not the only country in Europe. The epidemic is spreading with equal ferocity in Germany, France and Spain, with thousands of confirmed cases.
塞浦路斯出现首次确诊新冠肺炎病例，至此，欧盟27国均出现了冠状病毒确诊病例。
The first case of coronavirus was diagnosed in Cyprus, and all 27 EU countries have confirmed coronavirus cases.
欧盟已警告各成员国财长，新冠疫情暴发有可能使法国和意大利陷入衰退，而该疫情的长期流行则可能波及该区域金融市场，并造成主权债务和银行债务陷入恶性循环。
The European Union has warned finance ministers that an outbreak of the new crown could plunge France and Italy into recession, while a prolonged pandemic could spill over into the region's financial markets and plunge sovereign and bank debt into a vicious circle.
图5在度过“最伤心的一天”后，意大利的疫情没有丝毫缓解的趋势。
Fig. 5 After the "saddest day," Italy's epidemic shows no sign of abating.
单日新增病例再创新高，达到1797例。
The number of new cases reached a new high of 1797 a day.
意大利总理孔特当地时间3月9日晚宣布，人员流动紧急管控措施将推大至意大利全境。
Emergency measures to control the movement of people will be extended throughout Italy, Prime Minister Matteo Konte said on the night of March 9.
意大利全国学校继续停课至4月3日，同时暂停体育赛事与活动。
Schools throughout Italy continued to be closed until 3 April, while sporting events and activities were suspended.
但是！！！目前意大利的航班和火车仍在运行，金融、物流和航空服务都维持正常，政府、企业照常上班。
But!!! Italy's airlines and trains are still in operation, financial, logistics, and aviation services remain normal, and governments and businesses are working as usual.
超市、餐馆继续开放，只是要求顾客之间保留1米的距离，并不是完全意义上的“封城”，能否控制住疫情蔓延，仍待观察。
Supermarkets and restaurants continue to open, but customers to retain a 1-meter distance, is not the full meaning of the "closure", whether to control the spread of the epidemic remains to be seen.
意大利的死亡率仍然在盘旋在5%的高位。
Italy's mortality rate is still hovering around a high of 5%.
意大利民防部数据显示，大部分死亡案例集中在伦巴第大区，当地医疗系统已经不堪重负或是死亡率高的原因之一。
According to data from the Italian Ministry of Civil Defence, most deaths are concentrated in the Lombardy region, which is one of the reasons why the local health system is already overburdened or has a high mortality rate.
该地区约有一千万人口，因为缺乏床位，很多患者只能在医院走廊接受治疗。
The area has a population of about 10 million and many patients have to be treated in hospital corridors due to lack of beds.
根据我们以往数据推测，新增病死峰值通常比新增确诊病例的峰值滞后5-9天（详见：数说疫情0301）。
According to our previous data, the peak of new cases is usually 5-9 days behind the peak of newly diagnosed cases (see 0301 for more details).
而一旦形成类似武汉的“堰塞湖”，则峰值出现后病死率仍可能保持较高水平。
Once the formation of Wuhan-like "Yan Sehu," then peak disease death rate may remain high.
希望意大利政府能尽快采取更有效手段，以疫情防控为重，渡过难关。
We hope the Italian government will take more effective measures to prevent and control the disease and tide over the difficulties.
五、韩国警惕疫情反复，首尔出现集体感染图6韩国新增新冠肺炎确诊病例数持续呈下降趋势，主要是因为政府对于21万名“新天地”教会信徒的病毒检测工作已进入尾声。
South Korea Vigilance Against Repeated Outbreaks, Group Infections in Seoul Figure 6 The number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in South Korea continues to decline, mainly because the government is finalizing tests for 210,000 New World believers.
不过文在寅一再强调，目前切忌乐观，包括大邱、庆尚北道在内的多个地区仍在发生零星的小规模集体感染。
However, Wen stressed again and again that there was no room for optimism at the moment, with sporadic small-scale collective infections occurring in several areas, including Daegu and Gyeongshan North Province.
小规模集体感染事件持续出现，可能引发大规模集体感染事件，万万不可放松。
The persistence of small-scale mass infections with the potential to trigger mass infections must not be relaxed.
3月10日，首尔市西南部一间客服中心暴发疫情以来最大规模的集体感染，牵涉最少64人，病毒检测仍在进行中。
On March 10, the largest group infection since an outbreak at a customer service center in southwestern Seoul, involving at least 64 people, is ongoing.
六、伊朗亟待医疗物资援助图7伊朗最高领袖办公室发布声明称，受新冠肺炎疫情影响，伊朗最高领袖哈梅内伊将取消新年致辞，以避免聚集增加病毒传播风险。
Iranian Prime Minister Ayatollah Ali Khamenei will cancel his New Year's message because of the outbreak of pneumonia, in an effort to avoid gathering and increase the risk of spreading the virus, the Supreme Leader's Office said in a statement.
中国已通过红十字会等多个渠道向伊朗捐赠医疗物资。
China has donated medical supplies to Iran through the Red Cross and other channels.
世卫组织等国际组织也表示愿意支持伊朗解决医疗物资紧缺问题，未来或许将有更多种类和数量的医疗物资运达伊朗。
International organizations such as WHO have also expressed their willingness to support Iran's efforts to address the shortage of medical supplies, with more kinds and quantities of medical supplies likely to arrive in Iran in the future.
【特别说明：以上统计，2月28日前为世卫组织官方统计数据，数据截止时间为北京时间每日17时；从2月28日开始，数据由《财经》根据公开资料统计，截止时间为北京时间每日9时】七、全球疫情数字速览：1、【准备！1天2万人】日本厚生劳动省已经给全国的地方政府和医疗管理机构发出了一份紧急通知书，要求各地政府准备应对可能到来的大规模感染的问题，允许一般的医院也可以接纳新冠病毒感染者的诊治与住院治疗。
The Ministry of Health, Welfare and Labour has sent an urgent notice to local governments and medical authorities nationwide to prepare for possible mass infections and allow general hospitals to accept treatment and hospitalization for new cases of the virus.
通知称，东京都政府需要做好1天增加2万名感染者住院的医疗准备。
The notice said the government needed to prepare for the hospitalization of an additional 20,000 infected people a day.
大阪府也要做好一天接纳1万5000名感染者住院治疗的准备。
Osaka Prefecture is also preparing to receive 15,000 infected people a day for hospitalization.
2、【27所监狱发生暴动】上周末，意大利监狱为防控疫情限制探监，囚犯家属在监狱外进行抗议。
2007-9-24 15: 23 [hide] Italian prisons restricted visits over the weekend as families protested outside the prison to prevent and control the outbreak.
据美联社报道，当地时间3月8日至9日，疫情引发意大利27所监狱发生暴动，已造成6人死亡，另有50人越狱。
Rioting broke out in 27 Italian prisons between March 8 and 9, killing 6 people and breaking out of 50 others, AP reported.
3、【92.5%复工率】国家邮政局在全面落实中央疫情防控的有关要求前提下，自2月7日就有序启动了邮政快递业的复工复产工作。
The State Post Office has, since February 7, ordered the resumption of operations in the postal and courier industry, in full compliance with the requirements of the Central Prevention and Control of the Central Epidemic.
目前行业复工人数近300万人，复工率达到92.5%，日处理邮件快件稳定在1.6亿件以上，复产率超过80%。
At present, the number of workers returning to work is nearly 3 million, with a return-to-work rate of 92.5 per cent, and the daily processing rate of mail items has stabilized at more than 160 million items, with a recovery rate of over 80 per cent.
截至3月8日全行业承运寄递疫情防控物资1.73亿件，累计8.24万吨，发运车辆2.4万辆，货运班次350架次。
By March 8, the industry had shipped 173 million epidemic prevention and control materials, totaling 82,400 tons, 24,000 vehicles shipped and 350 cargo flights.
目标是到3月中旬除湖北地区外，行业的产能基本恢复到正常。
The goal is to return to normal capacity by mid-March, with the exception of Hubei province.
小结：今日上午，中国国家领导人出现在武汉战疫一线，安定民心、振奋士气，预示武汉歼灭战即将取得彻底胜利。
Summary: This morning, Chinese leaders appeared on the front lines of the Wuhan epidemic, calming the people's hearts and boosting morale, heralding the imminent victory of the Wuhan annihilation war.
疫情带来的恐慌导致全球金融市场震荡，美国各方仍在为如何应对疫情来回扯皮。
The panic caused by the outbreak has sent tremors through global financial markets, and the US continues to wrangle over how to deal with the epidemic.
意大利死亡率居高不下，封城举措尽管扩大至全国范围，但是否有效需要观察。
Italy's mortality rate remains high, and the effectiveness of the closure initiative, although extended nationwide, needs to be seen.
韩国上下仍在警惕疫情反复的可能。
South Korea is still wary of the possibility of repeated outbreaks.
